Shaco.name: Shaco
Shaco.title: the Demon Jester
Shaco.lore: Crafted long ago as a plaything for a lonely prince, the enchanted marionette Shaco now delights in murder and mayhem. Corrupted by dark magic and the loss of his beloved charge, the once-kind puppet finds pleasure only in the misery of the poor souls he torments. He uses toys and simple tricks to deadly effect, finding the results of his bloody “games” hilarious—and for those who hear a dark chuckle in the dead of night, the Demon Jester may have marked them as his next plaything.
Shaco.blurb: Crafted long ago as a plaything for a lonely prince, the enchanted marionette Shaco now delights in murder and mayhem. Corrupted by dark magic and the loss of his beloved charge, the once-kind puppet finds pleasure only in the misery of the poor souls...
allytips: Using Deceive over terrain can help you make a clean escape.
Try getting items with on-hit effects. These will also benefit your Hallucination clone.
Backstab's damage can be increased with increased Critical Damage effects like Infinity Edge.
enemytips: If Shaco is doing well early-game, it is worth the investment to place Stealth Wards near his Jungle camps.
If Shaco uses Deceive to enter a fight he won't be able to quickly use it again to get away. Work with your team to quickly focus him down.

spells.name: Deceive
spells.description:
Shaco becomes Invisible and teleports to target location.

His first attack while Invisible is empowered, dealing bonus damage and critically striking if he attacks from behind.
spells.tooltip:
Shaco teleports nearby and becomes Invisible for {{ stealthduration }} seconds. Shaco remains Invisible even if he uses Jack in the Box or Hallucinate.

His next basic attack during Invisibility deals {{ totaldamage }} bonus physical damage (this damage can crit). If attacking from behind, this attack also critically strikes for {{ f1 }}% damage.

Stealth - Invisible: Shaco can only be revealed by nearby enemy Turrets or True Sight.

spells.name: Jack In The Box
spells.description: Shaco creates a hidden animated Jack-in-the-Box. When triggered, it will fear and attack nearby enemies.
spells.tooltip:
Shaco creates a Jack in the Box that hides from view after {{ e5 }} seconds. It pops out when an enemy comes near or when uncovered by a ward or trinket, making nearby enemies flee very slowly for {{ e3 }} seconds ({{ minionfearduration }} seconds for minions and monsters).

It attacks all nearby enemies for {{ aoedamage }} magic damage, increased to {{ e1 }} (+{{ a1 }}) if it is attacking only one enemy. It lasts for {{ e4 }} (+{{ a2 }}) seconds while hidden or 5 seconds while firing.

spells.name: Two-Shiv Poison
spells.description: Shaco's Shivs passively poison targets on hit, slowing their movement speed. He can throw his Shivs to deal damage and poison the target. The thrown Shiv deals bonus damage if the target is below 30% health.
spells.tooltip:
Passive: While Two-Shiv Poison is ready to cast, Shaco's basic attacks reduce the target's Movement Speed by {{ slowamount*-100 }}% for {{ slowdurationpassive }} seconds.

Active: Shaco throws a shiv that deals {{ totaldamage }} magic damage and reduces the target's Movement Speed by {{ slowamount*-100 }}% for {{ slowdurationactive }} seconds. If the target has less than {{ executehealththreshold*100 }}% health, the shiv deals {{ executedamagepercent*100 }}% damage ({{ totalexecutedamage }} total).

spells.name: Hallucinate
spells.description: Shaco creates an illusion of himself near him, which can attack nearby enemies (Deals reduced damage to turrets).  Upon death, it explodes, spawning three mini Jack in the Boxes and dealing damage to nearby enemies.
spells.tooltip:
Shaco vanishes briefly and reappears with a clone. The clone lasts up to {{ clonelifetime }} seconds and detonates when it dies, dealing {{ explosiontotaldamage }} magic damage to nearby enemies and spawning three mini Jack in the Boxes that trigger immediately.

  • Mini boxes deal {{ aoedamage }} damage ({{ stdamage }} if attacking only one enemy) and make enemies flee for {{ boxfearduration }} second(s).
  • Clone deals {{ cloneaadamagepercent*100 }}% of Shaco's damage and receives {{ cloneincomingdamagepercent*100 }}% increased damage.

The clone can be controlled by holding the Alt key and using the Right Mouse button or by reactivating this ability.

passive.name: Backstab
passive.description: Shaco's basic attacks and Two-Shiv Poison deal additional damage when striking from behind.
passive.tooltip:
When striking from behind, Shaco's basic attack deals an additional {{ basicattackdamage }} physical damage and Two-Shiv Poison deals an additional {{ shivdamage }} magic damage.

Backstab's additional basic attack damage can crit.
